msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:321
msgid "The simplest option is to enter a list of terms where each one is its name. Its slug will be generated automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:322
msgid "This is entered as a list with no hierarchy. It is appropriate for either non-hierarchical taxonomies or a few entries of a hierarchical one."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:323
msgid "You can also enter entries hierarchically into a hierarchical taxonomy. For this, you need to indent the entries to identify the hierarchy of terms wanted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:324
msgid "In particular, you may want to add terms into an existing hierarchy. So to identify where the entries are to go, you need to enter the existing term (either name or slug) in the list with no indent - and then to follow it by the sub-tree of terms to be added."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:325
msgid "An implication of this is that it tries to identify if the term entered already exists and does not try to enter it again."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:326
msgid "Thus the count of terms added displayed will not be the number of lines present."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:327
msgid "Terms migrate"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-simpletaxonomyrefreshed-admin-import.php:328
msgid "The migrate tool allows you to copy existing terms of a taxonomy to pre-populate this screen for populating a taxonomy."
msgstr ""

